					<div class="post video internal p2 video jambox jawbone technology advertising hour10">
						<div class="right">
							<div class="tr"></div>
							<div class="left">
								<div class="tl"></div>
								<div class="content">
									<object width="500" height="308"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/XgC3zjNH1oU&amp;rel=0&amp;egm=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;fs=1"></param><param name="wmode" value="transparent"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/XgC3zjNH1oU&amp;rel=0&amp;egm=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="500" height="308" allowFullScreen="true" wmode="transparent"></embed></object><br /><br />
									<p><strong>JAMBOX</strong></p>
<p>So I go into the <a href="http://jawbone.com/">Jawbone</a> office a few months ago and they put this monolithic block of something on the table and the CEO Hosain Rahman turns on his iPad and hits play on a movie. And I&#8217;m seriously like &#8220;What the hell, man? Why you gotta make me pee myself like this? Is that entirely necessary? Could you have maybe just told me that you want to show me something I&#8217;ve never seen before and let me excuse myself to go into the restroom where an adult pees?&#8221;</p>
<p>But then I cleaned up and we started talking about the Jambox and why it sounds like nothing I&#8217;ve ever heard before. And then I got some amazing people together and made a video.</p>
<p>The DP is <a href="http://benjibakshi.com/">Benji Bakshi</a>. The guy is <a href="http://www.theofficialtetris.com/">Tetris Kelly</a>. Yes, <em>Tetris</em>. I cast him on his first ever audition. The music is JAMBOX Anthem by <a href="http://twitter.com/ilikepants">Deepak Mantena</a> (<a href="http://junkculture.biz/">Junk Culture</a>) and Big Shot by Tetris Kelly. The JAMBOX design is by <a href="http://www.fuseproject.com/">Yves Béhar</a>. The Big News by Hosain Rahman, naturally.</p>
<p>When this thing is in the Apple Store on the 16th, I think you&#8217;re going to want to give it a listen.</p>
